 INFO [bg.po] No Git `filter` attribute is set for *.po files on this path.
 INFO [bg.po]
 INFO [bg.po] The filter attribute describes how Git should normalize #: location comments on each
 INFO [bg.po] PO entry when you commit. Those comments change often as source files move; committing
 INFO [bg.po] their churn produces noisy diffs and inflates the repository.
 INFO [bg.po]
 INFO [bg.po] Setting filter=gettext-no-location or filter=gettext-no-line-number in .gitattributes
 INFO [bg.po] tells git-po-helper which location style you intend, so it can flag bad #: lines in
 INFO [bg.po] the PO (for example references that still include line numbers).
 INFO [bg.po]
 INFO [bg.po] Please configure the filter for XX.po, for example:
